        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 12:26AM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 1223 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
between Marion and Wytheville, or over Rural Retreat, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph. Heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Excessive rainfall may flood roadside
ditches causing debris to be washed onto the highway.
Flooding of poor drainage areas also possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wytheville...
Bland...
Rural Retreat...
Ceres...
Max Meadows...
Bastian...
and Marion Wytheville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning, especially along Interstate 81.</instruction>
